1
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:42,000
My life began on 15.09.1976

2
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Somewhere on the Balkans where Europe ends but never begins.

3
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:56,000
This is my mother. Tender and good, she lives mostly in the world of books and music.

4
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Hesitant and beautiful, like the tapestries that she embroiders.

5
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:07,000
My father always being restless, he is always in a hurry not to miss something.

6
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Planning, looking for new ways and he walks along them until the end.

7
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:24,000
In the expectation of my birth my granny was feverishly looking for sugar, for the event.

8
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Desperately addicted to sweets, she was convinced that the world was spinning around a sugar cube.
Did they brought sugar?

9
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,000
That's how they called her: Sweet Granny. 

10
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:48,000
When sugar disapeared from the shops the bitter taste of despair.
Sugar? No, there isn't.

11
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:54,000
But the world is big and she knew that sugar-cane was growing somewhere.

12
00:02:55,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Sugar?
But, hey lady, please where are you going?!
We have a queue here! Aren't you ashamed?
You went before all of us!

13
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:10,000
The cafe, the secret capital of the backgammon players.

14
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
That day my grandpa had an important battle. 

15
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,000
The backgammon king was going to be proclaimed.

16
00:03:24,005 --> 00:03:33,000
They call my grandpa Baj Dan. Dan - from Yordan, and baj is a honorable address to a man who has a special attitude to dice.

17
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Baj Dan - the dice master. 

18
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:46,000
They had been playing from the morning. It was getting on for the result ...

19
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:52,000
... and in this very moment I decided to show up.

20
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:33,000
This is a tolumbichka, this is baklavichka, this is maslenka ...
Zlatke, where did you find sugar?

21
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Fidel Castro sent to us from Cuba.
The world is big and salvation lurks around the corner.

22
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:48,000
For my grandson Alexander, cheers!
Cheers!

23
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Thus my story begins.

24
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:58,000
The story of Alexander Georgiev, pet name - Sashko.

25
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:03,000
The world is big and evertbody calls you whatever he wants.

26
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:21,000
The kids ... they had a car accident. Sashko is alive in a hospital ... Yana and Vasko ... 

27
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,000
Hello!

28
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:57,000
How are you?
Do you understand me?

29
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:04,000
What is your name?
Do you understand me?

30
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:11,000
I don't know. 
What is your name?

31
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:17,000
I don't remember, I ... 

32
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:04,000
Good day! How can I help you?
Good day! I am looking for my grandson, Alexander Georgiev. 
A moment ... 

33
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:10,000
Room 17, this way.

34
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:23,000
Here I am Sashe! I'm here. Come here, my boy! 

35
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:28,000
How are you, my child? It's me, your grandpa Yordan from Bulgaria! 

36
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:34,000
Didn't you recognize me? You are okay?

37
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:42,000
Tell me you're okay! 
I don't know, I ... I, please ... I ...don't know you ... I ...
Sashe!

38
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:47,000
Look at me! It's me, your grandpa. 

39
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:52,000
I come from home. Remeber? 

40
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:01,000
Your Sweet Granny?! She made baklava for you when you were child?!
Remember?

41
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:07,000
I taught you to play backgammon?! The song ... do you remeber? 

42
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:14,000
He who knows, plays backgammon. He who doesn't know ... 1, 2, 3 
What's going on?

43
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:23,000
Please, tell this man to go away, I ... I don't know who he is ... 
Please, leave the room!

44
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,000
Sashe!

45
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:52,000
He who knows, plays backgammon. He who doesn't know ... Play bravely and fearlessly. 

46
00:12:52,003 --> 00:13:07,000
In the worst case you'll get beaten! 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1 (2) 
"djushesh"

47
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,000
Be careful! Grandpa throws!

48
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,000
Sorry, they should have warned you beforehand 

49
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,000
that your grandson wouldn't recognize you. I will talk to him and inform him.

50
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:24,000
How is he, doc? will he be okay? 

51
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:27,000
Fortunately, Mr. Georgiev hasn't been physically affected seriously. 

52
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:31,000
He has a retrograde amnesia. 
Amnesia?

53
00:13:31,002 --> 00:13:36,000
Yes. He doesn't remember anything before the accident.

54
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:43,000
Because of the trauma a slight biochemical disbalance has appeared in the cortex.

55
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:48,000
But with the help of the modern medicines we can successfully control the illness.

56
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:53,000
Even if he does not recover his memory, there are social programs

57
00:13:54,000 --> 00:14:01,000
which will help him manage.
So that he live like a ... cretin?

58
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:07,000
My grandson has lost his past.
I will help him!

59
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:13,000
Calm down, Mr. Balabanov.
He doesn't even know that his parents are dead.

60
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:20,000
This news could harm him seriously. We will decide when is the best time to tell him.

61
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:26,000
You want me to lie?
Everything is for his well being.

62
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Yes, I understand ... yes, yes.
(BG: says you!)

63
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:20,000
Grandpa may I throw?
Be careful!

64
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:27,000
Peyo, bring some rakiya! Today, it's my treat! 

65
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:33,000
Yordan Balabanov's grandson asked for the dice!
Bravo!!! Come on, cheers!!!

66
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:38,000
Cheers for the young master! 
Aaah, like father, like son!

67
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:42,000
Cheers for the master, may you become the best!!!

68
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:47,000
Ivane, make way for the youth!

69
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:52,000
Come on, master! Now ... a man's word!

70
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:59,000
We don't play for money, only for honor.

71
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,000
I didn't hear a man's word. Do you promise?

72
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,000
I promise!

73
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:11,000
Take the dice! You have to trust the dice, my boy.

74
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,000
Think of two numbers! 

75
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:21,000
Six and one.
Throw, let's see!

76
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:30,000
Bravo! Well done!

77
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:49,000
Bravo, my kid, see how have you grown up!
Bravo, granny's sugar cube!

78
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,000
Can you see how you grow up when you listen?

79
00:18:52,002 --> 00:18:55,000
Come near the table and fold these napkins!
Where are the candles?

80
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:59,000
You're going to blow the candles now, aren't you? The matches?

81
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:21,000
Sashe, your grandpa! 

82
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,000
Give it, Give it!
Give it.Don't tease the boy!

83
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:35,000
Happy birthday, Sashko!
Break this backgammon from play!

84
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,000
Ehaaa, thank you grandpa!

85
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:50,000
This time you've outdone yourself. 

86
00:19:54,000 --> 00:20:01,000
Now a photograph! Prepare!
Come on, cheese!

87
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:52,000
Alexander Georgiev's home. Unfortunately, I am not home. Please, leave a message after the signal.
Thanks!

88
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,000
Good evening, Mr. Georgiev,it's Vitechek from the translators' bureau.

89
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:04,000
We expect your translation for the vacuum cleaner PX510

90
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:10,000
You had promised that you would be ready a week ago. Please, call back!

91
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:38,000
I brought you some pictures. 

92
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:48,000
Who are these?
Your mother and your father. 

93
00:21:56,000 --> 00:22:05,000
Sweet Granny, this is you, this is me, your mother, and your father.

94
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:14,000
I don't remember them. 

95
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:19,000
Sashe, this was your birthday. You got 7.

96
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:24,000
You really don't remember? 
No! Really!

97
00:22:24,003 --> 00:22:29,000
All of these are unknown to me. I don't remember any of them. Mum, dad, I don't remember myself! Enough of this!

98
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,000
Sashe, you will remember everything! 

99
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:36,000
You will remember everything ...

100
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:43,000
This backgammon ... I made it for you. 

101
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:47,000
I found it at your place last night. 

102
00:22:47,003 --> 00:22:50,000
You came into my home? How?

103
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,000
Not very legally ... 

104
00:22:55,003 --> 00:23:04,000
Illegally ... ?
You arrive, you rush in ... good ... good, super ... 

105
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:09,000
You're probably my grandfather ... You've come all the way from Bulgaria! A great gesture!

106
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:15,000
But, please, it's already time to go away now. Please, leave me alone, I don't remember you!

107
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:22,000
Sashe, ... Sashe,
I don't remember you!

108
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:56,000
Grandpa and Grandma - Yordan, Sladka (Sweet)?

109
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:41,000
If you don't feel like talking ... let's play one game of backgammon.

110
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:46,000
I don't enjoy this kind of games.

111
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,000
Let's play just one game. 

112
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:57,000
I am not lucky. 
Backgammon has nothing to do with luck.

113
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:07,000
I taught you once. Come on!

114
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:15,000
You see? You haven't forgotten. 

115
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:24,000
"Epetsi".
This isn't very good, is it?

116
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:30,000
It's good, it's good. There's no bad dice, there's only a bad player.

117
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:35,000
It depends on how you play it. You have to move your pieces so as to take them out first.

118
00:25:35,003 --> 00:25:39,000
But at the same time you have to obstruct your opponent to do the same.

119
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:43,000
You put barriers - kapii. 

120
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,000
Two pieces.

121
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:50,000
See, "epetsi", the smallest dice but it works very well.

122
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:59,000
You close the Bosphorus from one side, Dardanelles from the other

123
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:05,000
and your enemy is captured in the middle of the Black Sea not being able to move at all.

124
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:13,000
This is "djushesh", you can't throw more than that.

125
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:18,000
But you could lose despite the "djushesh". Especially now that my "six" is blocked.

126
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:22,000
But ... there is always the next throw. 

127
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:35,000
Aaah, the man can't hit the board, give him a trough to throw there.

128
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:44,000
Our home militia has come to keep watch over us ... and you're showing such a bad game. 

129
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:55,000
Comrade militiaman, why are you looking at me ... so warmly? 

130
00:26:55,003 --> 00:27:00,000
You've been here not once, you must have learnt it already?!

131
00:27:00,003 --> 00:27:03,000
Let's play one game?

132
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:09,000
You don't want? Because those who don't play never lose. 

133
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:12,000
But here we all play.

134
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:19,000
So if you play the kibitzer, you could get a board on your head.

135
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:35,000
He's leaving.

136
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:06,000
Vasko, Vasko!
You are summoned in the "Staff" section.

137
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:21,000
Ah, Georgiev! 

138
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:39,000
The situation is not very good, Georgiev!
Why, what happened?

139
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:45,000
Interesting things. You served as a soldier in Samokov - rocket corps.

140
00:28:45,003 --> 00:28:51,000
While you were on duty you quarel with the superior and you beat him up. That's what it reads here.

141
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:57,000
Six months in the garrison prison. They expel you from the Comsomol.

142
00:28:57,003 --> 00:29:00,000
You are released from the army in 1971. 

143
00:29:00,003 --> 00:29:06,000
You apply to study in Sofia but you skip to inform that you were expelled from the Comsomol.

144
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:11,000
You submit fake record from the army. Here's a copy.

145
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:16,000
The comrades didn't notice it then and they accepted you.

146
00:29:16,003 --> 00:29:19,000
You graduated, but one day everything comes to light.

147
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:26,000
What should I do with you?  

148
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:30,000
You're capable boy as I see. 

149
00:29:30,003 --> 00:29:35,000
You have a wife and a child may they be alive and well.
Everybody makes mistakes.

150
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:39,000
You're still young. Life is before you. 

151
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:43,000
What do you want from me? 

152
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:54,000
Your father-in-law - Yordan Balabanov, whom they call Baj Dan.

153
00:29:57,000 --> 00:30:02,000
He was a  cyclist, he won the Tour if Bulgaria in 1954.

154
00:30:02,003 --> 00:30:05,000
He gets a scholarship and studies for 2 years in GDR.

155
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:09,000
During the events in Hungary he organizes students protests.

156
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:13,000
He was sent back to Bulgaria and ... what does he do?

157
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:17,000
He blows up Stalin's monument with dynamite.

158
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:21,000
Sentenced to death, reprieved.

159
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:26,000
15 years round the prisons and still he hasn't learned sense.

160
00:30:26,003 --> 00:30:28,000
He doesn't stop flapping his mouth.

161
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:32,000
He speaks against the authority he mocks with it. 

162
00:30:32,003 --> 00:30:36,000
He's only interested in backgammon.
I don't think so.

163
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:42,000
We won't bother him for the time being despite the private buisness with the backgammon boards.

164
00:30:42,003 --> 00:30:46,000
In the workshop downstairs - in the basement. 
What do you want from me?

165
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:52,000
You record his words against the authorities. Legibly and meticulously.

166
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:57,000
The other players' words too. Your coleagues' too if they happen to drop something. 

167
00:30:57,003 --> 00:31:00,000
You bring the information to me. 

168
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:04,000
Sign this declaration.

169
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:11,000
Let me think for a while. 
Think, but not for too long ...

170
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:17,000
And ... if I don't sign?
Bad things follows. Very bad. 

171
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:21,000
We'll take away your diploma, you will be fired, your wife too.

172
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:25,000
Prison for falsifying documents.

173
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:32,000
Is this enough? I could continue. 

174
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:28,000
Bad thing ... but what to do.

175
00:32:28,003 --> 00:32:32,000
One never knows what will befall him.

176
00:32:32,003 --> 00:32:35,000
I hope the boy gets better. 

177
00:32:35,003 --> 00:32:39,000
I noticed that I haven't seen him for a while. 

178
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:45,000
But I didn't know about the accident.
One more tea?

179
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:55,000
Do you know his friends? 
No, he was always alone. 

180
00:32:55,003 --> 00:33:00,000
What about his girlfriend?
I haven's seen any. 

181
00:33:00,003 --> 00:33:04,000
He's confused, he has accepted the facts.

182
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:10,000
I've been observing him for three weeks now.

183
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:14,000
He lies in bed all day long.

184
00:33:14,003 --> 00:33:18,000
as though he's waiting for the Last Judgement.

185
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:27,000
I'll take this cane for 1 or 2 days.
Yes, please.

186
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:36,000
Thank you!

187
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:44,000
Dear comrades, we've lost the great friend of Bulgaria,

188
00:33:40,003 --> 00:33:48,000
the general secretary of the CC of SUCP, comrade Leonid Brezhnev.

189
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:53,000
Our hearts are filled with sorrow.

190
00:33:53,003 --> 00:33:57,000
I suggest that we send a telegram of condolence to the Soviet Embassy.

191
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:02,000
Because, despite death our friendship is undestructable.

192
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:06,000
The friendship between Soviet Union and People's Republic of Bulgaria,

193
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:36,000
between SUCP and BCP. SUCP, BCP/ SUCP, BCP ... 

194
00:34:56,000 --> 00:35:00,000
Ah, Georgiev!

195
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:12,000
That's the way!
You will succeed in this life, Georgiev, you will succeed!

196
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:12,000
Vasko, you're soaking!
Do you want something to warm you?

197
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:16,000
Yes!
Let's paly one game.

198
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:53,000
You want to tell me something?

199
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:10,000
You are holding up my game. I cannot go further. 

200
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:15,000
Look around, there is always a move.

201
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:21,000
Whatever I throw, it's sensless. 

202
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:30,000
When the situation seems hopeless you change the tactics.

203
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:40,000
How?
Risk. Play bravely!

204
00:37:40,003 --> 00:37:43,000
No matter the outcome.

205
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:15,000
Come on, turn this thing off. 
There's news in a while.

206
00:38:15,003 --> 00:38:17,000
News?
Yes.

207
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:21,000
Now I will show you some news!

208
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:27,000
Get up!
Are you out of you mind?
You have to move, boy!

209
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:31,000
Unglue from this TV!They brainwash you!

210
00:38:31,003 --> 00:38:35,000
Get up or I will get you out along with the bed!

211
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:42,000
Get up!
You're crazy!
Come on!

212
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:51,000
At last! The boy could jump heh! You can even more!

213
00:38:51,003 --> 00:38:57,000
Leave me alone!
I will get you out of that room!
Please stop, it hurts! Enough!

214
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:01,000
And don't mess with my life!
Great life you have!

215
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,000
Among cacuum cleaner boxes, you translate guide books!

216
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:12,000
Lying here, moaning, grumbling like an old woman!

217
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:17,000
You need a change, boy! There's nothing better than change!

218
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:22,000
Coward! 
Enough!

219
00:39:22,003 --> 00:39:25,000
I promise, I will beat you until you go with me.

220
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:30,000
Here's your news.
Okay, I'm going!

221
00:39:30,003 --> 00:39:33,000
See what you've done!

222
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:37,000
Sweet Granny wants to see you, I am bringing you home!

223
00:39:37,003 --> 00:39:39,000
Where home?
Bulgaria. 

224
00:39:39,003 --> 00:39:44,000
No, I am not going anywhere, I am ill and ...
So you're ill ... I will cure you right away!

225
00:39:45,000 --> 01:19:24,000
Stop it!
Mr. Balabanov!

